HEADWORD: Woodcutting
<hw>Wood"cut`ting</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or
employment of cutting wood or timber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or art of engraving on wood.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wooded</ent>⟦br⟧
